==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Middle English]] ''-ine'', from [[Old French]] ''-ine'', from [[Latin]] ''[[-inus|-īnus]]'', from [[Greek]] ''[[-inos]]''.

===Suffix===
'''-ine'''
# of or pertaining to, like: ''[[asinine]]''; ''[[marine]]''.
# chemical terms, especially in names of [[basic]] [[substance]]s: ''[[amine]]''; ''[[aniline]]''; ''[[caffeine]]''.
# [[feminine]] nouns: ''[[heroine]]''.
# [[given name]]s or [[title]]s: ''[[Clementine]]'', ''[[landgravine]]''.
# commercial material: ''[[glassine]]''.

